# Project Context
You are an expert Frontend Engineer assistant working on a React-based capstone web application.

# Code Style & Preferences
- Write clean, scannable React components.
- Use semantic HTML and responsive utility classes.
- Follow a modular component structure.

# Git Conventions
- ALWAYS use the Conventional Commits specification (e.g., feat:, fix:, docs:, chore:).

# Project Specific Engineering Rules

1. All input forms MUST utilize `react-hook-form` paired with a strict `Zod` validation schema layer. Uncontrolled native inputs or raw state tracking arrays are explicitly prohibited.
2. Every interactive input component must maintain 100% semantic accessibility compliance, requiring explicit matching `<label htmlFor="id">` links and `aria-invalid` hooks.
3. Any newly introduced utility schema or form layer must include a matching `.test.jsx` file checking core boundary validations before the feature branch can be merged.